<div></div> <div>K</div> <div>B</div> <div></div> <div>R</div> </div>
<i>Position after 4. Qe2</i>
</div>

<p>

<i>Modern Chess Openings</i>, back when we would use a huge thick
book to go over openings, points out Black’s best course of action at
this point is 4...Qe7 5. Qxe4 d6 6. d4, but even here White is up a 
pawn.

<p>

My opponent could see his knight was in trouble, so he responded
with a counter threat, <b>4. f6?</b>, giving us this:

