<p>

When I showed the people at the chess club later on that week this game,
my brother suggested that I take the rook with 7. Qxh8.  A chess master,
a mentor for us, looked at him and said “you don’t go for the rook in 
chess.  You go for the <i>king</i>!”.

<p>

Anyway, back to the game, which continued like this:

<p>

<b>7. Qxg6+ Ke7 8. Qxe4+ Kd6? 9. Qd4+?</b> (better was 9. d4!) <b>Kc6?</b>

